<p>I'm currently using the <a href="https://github.com/wankdanker/node-odbc" rel="nofollow">node-odbc</a> to connect to our SQL Server database. This is in a node.js API. It's a pretty standard connection. I pass in the query and an array of parameters (params). The problem is when I have rather large amounts of text within a parameter. Over 4000 characters.</p>  <pre><code>db.open(cn, function (err) {         if (err) {             console.log(req.fullPath);             console.log(JSON.stringify({'Error': err.toString() }));             res.writeHead(500, 'Internal Server Error', {'content-type': 'application/vnd.collection+json'});             res.end(JSON.stringify({Error: req.SystemErrors.GetError(req.SystemErrors.ErrorConnectingToDatabase)}));             return;         }          db.query(query, params, function (err, data) {             if (err) {                 res.writeHead(500, 'Internal Server Error', {'content-type': 'application/vnd.collection+json'});                 res.end(JSON.stringify({Error: req.SystemErrors.GetError(req.SystemErrors.ErrorRunningQuery)}));                 return;             } else if (typeof data[0] === 'undefined') {                 res.writeHead(200, 'OK', {'content-type': 'application/vnd.collection+json'});                 res.end(JSON.stringify({ 'Message': 'No data returned for this request.' }));                 return;             } else {                 next(data);             }              db.close(function (err) {                 if (err) {                     res.writeHead(500, 'Internal Server Error', {'content-type': 'application/vnd.collection+json'});                     res.end(JSON.stringify({Error: req.SystemErrors.GetError(req.SystemErrors.ErrorClosingDatabaseConnection)}));                 }             });         });     }); </code></pre>  <p>I ran into this issue when trying to pass over a large XML variable type to my stored procedure in MS SQL Server. I did a trace on the data being passed over and node-odbc interpreted this XML as an NVARCHAR(4000), thus truncating the value stored in this variable.</p>  <p>So my question is, how can I tell node-odbc the variable type (XML, VARCHAR(MAX), ect) OR set the length of of the variable? As always, Thanks for any info!</p>